  <description><![CDATA[<ul>
<li><span><span><a data-udi="umb://document/45eb7a7fa1e543fda7d1ac4ddecafb79" href="/{localLink:umb://document/45eb7a7fa1e543fda7d1ac4ddecafb79}" title="Ski lift pass offers">Lift pass offer:</a> Free lift pass included with your stay at Hotel Terrace, available all season - Please see our lift pass offers page for more details </span></span></li>
<li><span>Resort altitude of 1,000 metres</span></li>
<li><span>82 kilometres of slopes</span></li>
<li><span>43 kilometres of cross country tracks</span></li>
<li><span>2 hours 15 minutes transfer from Zurich Airport </span></li>
</ul>
<p><span>Located 25km south of Lake Lucerne in a wide mountain valley, Engelberg is the biggest and, according to the locals, the most stunning ski resort in central Switzerland. With slopes stretching across 2000 meters, you've got tons of space for snowboarding, skiing, and even sledding, as well as a range of other activities to keep your winter holiday full of excitement and fun. </span></p>
<h2>Skiing and snowboarding in Engelberg</h2>
<p><span>When it comes to the main skiing area of Engelberg, you'll find that the majority of the pistes are spread out due to the glaciers and the rugged landscape of resort. Engelberg's ski area offers around 82 kilometres of skiable terrain and is divided into two main sectors: Titlis-Stand and Jochpass. Here, the elevated north-facing slopes hold onto their snow really well, ensuring a lengthy ski season. Plus, the piste grooming is top-notch, providing excellent skiing and snowboarding conditions. </span><span>You'll find that the area caters well for intermediates to advanced as many of the runs are challenging steep reds. The Jochpass region tends to be less crowded compared to Titlis, offering pleasant blue and red runs for you to enjoy, some of which are wonderfully long, taking you all the way down to the valley station. However, if you are a beginner, you're in luck - there's a dedicated beginner's area at Gerschnialp, along with smaller areas at Trübsee and Untertrübsee, where you can start off by building your confidence. </span>Boarders are also in for a treat as Engerlberg offers some fantastic freeriding opportunity and many guides available to accompany you and show you the best spots.   </p>
<h2>Where to stay in Engelberg</h2>
<p><span>When it comes to finding the perfect place to stay in Engelberg, you're in for a treat as Engelberg offers a range of accommodations to suit every preference and budget. We offer two accommodations in Engelberg, Hotel Terrace and Residence Titlis Resort, both of which are 3 stars. Residence Titlis Resort offers modern and comfortable apartments, located in the heart of resort with the centre only a short minute walk away. Hotel Terrace offers a range of spa and wellness with treatments and massages available and even includes your lift pass in your stay!</span></p>
<h2>Bars and restaurants in Engelberg</h2>
<p><span>Engelberg's mountain restaurants and bars bring you a delightful array of refreshment choices. Whether you're craving traditional Swiss favourites; cheese fondue, crispy pizzas, or cold platters, or a simple hot drink to warm you up, you'll find it all in this resort. No matter which mountain restaurant or bar you visit, they all share one incredible feature: a breath-taking view of the surrounding mountains that will undoubtedly captivate you. Whether you're taking a break from skiing or enjoying a mountain adventure, you can indulge in delicious local delicacies, warm and welcoming hospitality, and don't miss the chance to experience age-old traditions in some of the charming traditional huts dotted around.</span></p>
<h2>What's included in an Inghams holiday to Engelberg</h2>
<p><span>Flights, transfers and accommodation based on self catering, bed and breakfast, half board. Optional add ons include equipment hire, lift pass and tuition, please see the 'Ski extras' tab below for more information on these.</span></p>]]></description>
