  <thingsToDo><![CDATA[<h2><strong>Things to do in Engelberg </strong></h2>
<h3>Restaurants, food and drink </h3>
<p><span>Restaurants are distributed evenly throughout the ski resort of Engelberg with the majority consisting of cosy huts serving Swiss specialities - But you can also find very good international cuisine throughout resort as well. Throughout the village and ski area there are several good places to stop for a break. </span><span>The Panorama-Restaurant located on the Titlis peak at 3,020 metres is an excellent place to pit stop during your skiing day and offers some incredible views and a great selection of wines. The </span><span>Skihütte Stand found in the Stand station at 2,428 metres has a large sun terrace so you can enjoy local swiss delicacies with a great view of the glacier.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-size: 16.38px;">Après, bars, clubs and nightlife</span></h3>
<p><span>Engelberg offers a diverse range of après-ski choices and can get very lively during weekends. Located at the base of the primary ski lift, the Chalet après-ski bar stands out as a favoured destination to locals and guests. The Ski Lodge and Yucatan bars are some other well-known establishments within resort, And if you're looking for some night-time excitement you might want to explore the Spindle nightclub for a fun evening experience with friends.</span></p>
<h3>Spas and relaxation </h3>
<p><span>The Kempinski Palace Spa is open to all and offers a sanctuary of relaxation and rejuvenation for your winter holiday. </span><span>The spa's facilities are designed to cater to every need, from soothing massages and invigorating treatments to state-of-the-art wellness experiences, all with a stunning backdrop of the majestic peaks.</span></p>
<h3>Shopping </h3>
<p><span>Engelberg offers a delightful shopping experience where you can find a blend of traditional Swiss craftsmanship and contemporary boutiques. Explore stores that showcase Swiss watches, artisanal chocolates, and top-notch outdoor gear. And let's not forget the cosy souvenir shops filled with alpine trinkets and keepsakes. Whether you're on the lookout for luxurious Swiss treasures or simply want to take a piece of the alpine charm home with you, Engelberg's shopping scene has something to offer everyone against the backdrop of its awe-inspiring natural beauty.</span></p>
<h2><strong>Engelberg resort activities </strong></h2>
<h3>Titlis Cliff Walk </h3>
<p>Located across from the Titlis Summit Station, test out your fear of heights with Europe's highest suspension bridge at a whopping 3,041 metres! Put down the skis and take a moment to appreciate the views of the surrounding mountains and glaciers - if you dare.</p>
<h3>Glacier Cave </h3>
<p><span>A magical world of ice awaits you - Engelberg's Glacier Cave </span><span>forms the frosty heart of Titlis and the ice here is up to 5,000 years old. The entrance is located on the first floor of the mountain station and entry is free so we'd highly recommend checking it out.</span></p>
<h3><span>Ice Flyer</span></h3>
<p><span>The Ice Flyer chair lift is a perfect way to see the parts of the mountains the slopes don't reach. Here, you'll sweep over untouched snow fields and icy depths with crevasses up to 20 metres deep - so make sure you bring your camera as you'll see some incredible views.</span></p>
<h3><span>Titlis Rotair</span></h3>
<p><span>This cable car rotates it's way up towards the snow covered summit of  Titlis and is the world's first revolving cable car. Thanks to it's 360 degree viewpoint, during your 5 minute journey you can expect idyllic panoramic views of the snow covered mountains, steep rock faces</span><span> and the larger ski area.</span></p>
<h3><span>Chocolate shop</span></h3>
<p><span>If you'd like a more laid back activity that's still fun and sweet, take a trip to the Titlis chocolate shop. Here you can immerse yourself in over 300 different specialities of chocolate, or if you can't decide, simply make your own!</span></p>]]></thingsToDo>
